Certainly, here are five example sentences in Serbian that use the word "mr" in different forms and positions. The word "mr" does not exist in the Serbian language, so I will assume you meant "mir", which means "peace" in English.

1. *Mir* je najvažnija stvar za ljude. (Peace is the most important thing for people.)
2. Ljudi često teže *miru* nakon sukoba. (People often strive for peace after conflict.)
3. Upravo sada uživam u *miru* i tišini svog doma. (Right now, I'm enjoying the peace and quiet of my home.)
4. *Mir* u svetu je cilj svake države. (World peace is the goal of every country.)
5. Ova organizacija se bori za *mir* i ljudska prava. (This organization fights for peace and human rights.)